2020-21 Planner with a 2-date spread view! It has daily, weekly and monthly pages as well as convenient hyperlinks in every page for quick navigation.

Andre Hryshchenko is a designer, photographer and an Apple evangelist. He got his first iPad for his wife to draw and accidentally discovered the world of digital planners! He has since then joined the paperless movement.
A Highly interactive yet simple planner brought to you guys specially by Raluca! Be inspired!

Raluca has a solid background in architecture and product design. Raluca uses her skills to make life easier, fun and a lot more productive. She builds productivity products like Master Planners, Hobby Journals and more!
Physiology booklets, with beautiful illustrations, highlights, and flashcards—a med student's favorite buddy. Be inspired!
Maddison Brennan is a first year med student. She loooves to doodle & illustrate, aims to see the world, and wants to work for WHO someday.
A minimalistic digital planner that allows you to focus on what matters, taking notes. Optimized for Retina Displays!

Tom Solid is the founder of the #PaperlessMovement, and a Noteshelf lover. He has always been dreaming of a green future, where technology meets nature! We both share the same vision - taking the concept of going paperless a notch higher every day!
The best part of any vacation is PLANNING IT! Here is a pretty Travel Planner from TypeMaven. Travel the world. Inspire!
Type Maven is a little haven that features modern digital planners, journals, notebooks and high-quality clipart. It was created by Marina Duque, a graphic designer from Toronto, Canada.
Plan, create, inspire, repeat. - the mantra that Whitney believes in. Follow her in her journey to a more creative, productive & happy life! Be inspired!
She is the voice & content creator for, Life by Whitney. In July, 2016, she discovered the Bullet Journal® and so began her bujo journey - plans, trackers, lists, designs, ideas, and more!
Oscar Campo's creative rendition of spiritual wisdom are now available as downloadable booklets. Stunning doodles & sketchnotes inside, be inspired!
Son of God, husband, father, engineer, sketchnoter, illustrator. He is a noteshelf-er since the initial days. His sketchnotes, #WisdomTips are absolutely stunning!
A clickable weekly planner and clipboard to jot down your notes, to do's, dreams, stickers and just about everything. Be inspired!

Hadge is a therapist and a mindfulness coach from Brighton, United Kingdom. He is a jack of many trades—loves to write, draw, paint, play some soulful tunes in the piano and the guitar. He started maintaining pen and paper journals and now moved on to digital journals.
Indulge yourself in a nostalgic loop of vintage flourishing and typography—here is a Penmanship Practice Booklet from Valerie. Be Inspired!

Valerie has fallen in love with digital scrapbooking and vintage ephemera! She collects books, post cards and paper products from the late 1800’s and early 1900’s and bring them alive by incorporating them into functional items on iPad.
A beautiful digital planner in Spanish with separate tabs for doodles, braindump, lectures, notes. Be inspired!

Meet Ari Alvarez. A designer, a sketchnote artist, and a journaler. She initially created this mindfulnessplanner to track everything - the daily tasks, thoughts, meditations and pretty much anything she likes. The versatility of this planner prompted her to share it with fellow Noteshelfers!
Beautiful planner with a purple-tone and 10 customizable tabs. Go create your planner just that way you want. Be inspired!
A mommy of 2 who uses her planner to sort homeschooling tasks, quilting & sewing projects, and tracking my language learning. She loves making various planner templates and stickers.
It is a pretty, customizable planner with soothing pastel colors. Be inspired by the soft and delicate feeling it emanates!
Patricia has always loved to paint, sing and knit since she was 5 years old! Her digital planners are not just pretty but customizable too!
Weekly planners with visually stunning title pages. Here is a bujo template by Cindy, adopt this or create your own. Be inspired!

Cindy is from France. She has always been interested in arts and crafts : drawing, calligraphy, painting, and photography. She is a freelance translator and she uses Bujo for tracking her personal and professional life. She loves watching zombies and alien movies/TV shows! Her creative renditions are a visual treat!
Susan's digital planners and bujos are for the digital savvy and simplicity loving folk! Adopt this or create your own, be inspired!

Susan is from Butte, Montana. She spends her time creating forms for Greenfield Printers for the past 17 years. She says she is a student for life and does this to hone her skills. One super-intelligent and creative grandma she is!
Check out these spreads from cursedjournal. Moodboard, reading log, and minimal planners - not so cursed, but absolutely delightful. Be inspired!
Sanae, calls herself overthinker pro. But, we know she is a pro doodler! You'll fall in love with the simplicity of her bujos and the cute little characters.
Take control of your life - spend smart, sleep well. These beautifully designed trackers will help take control of your life. Be inspired!

A data scientist and a brilliant bujoist! She speaks English, 5 Asian languages and French. She watches a lot of Netflix, BBT, Modern Family; and DC heroes shows are her favs. When she is not binge watching these, she practices wushu! She is a bag of surprises!
Simple yet colorful is what you can expect in Claire's planners. If you love simplicity with a dab of pleasing colors, draw inspirations from this!
She is the face behind 'Heart Handmade UK'. She and her team provide high ROI DIY tutorials that you can make quickly and easily. You’ll really enjoy them!
Gregory Koberger draws inspirations from startup stories and interprets them in his awesome visual note-taking style. Try sketch-noting, be inspired!

Greg hails from the lovely town of Schaghticoke (pronounced scat-a-coke) in upstate New York. After attending RIT he made the move to San Francisco where he’s worked for Mozilla, and freelanced for a bunch of startups.
He is an entrepreneur, designer, coder and is a founder of Readme.io
Spaceships can't maneuver through the millions of asteroids in an asteroid belt. They will be severely damaged. Myth or truth?
Ravali is our in-house testing-ninja. She just recently showed us that she is an awesome artist too! Check out her doodle art and planners here!
'Sun-salutations' for a healthy global community! A 'Noteshelf Original' production for International Yoga Day 2018. Be Inspired!

Kailas & Ravali were excited to ink this out! Kailas is an artist at heart, storyteller, and marketer by profession. He is also our in-house noisemaker! Ravali is our in-house testing-ninja and a gifted illustrator. She is a chocoholic and loves to doodle.
